subSubSection.paragraph:
A large genus with 57 species, 12 of which occur in Ecuador. Most species are small with various red or blue and black color patterns, some species with green stripes (
Figs. 30a & b
). The latest revision with illustrated keys is by Garrison (2009); Machado (2010) provided an update. Most species inhabit weed-choked ponds, marshes and swamps with floating aquatic plants, some in deeply shaded forest.

